1 Antwort

  • Robert Klnky 10.06.2016
    The project MOBILLI is a tele-operated robot that aims to provide users more freedom to move around in the remote place. It deploys smartphone as both microcontroller and video communication interface. When user A attaches a smartphone to MOBILLI, it activates the wireless connec-tion to the user B as well. User B can control the movement of MOBILLI in 5-axis through gestural instruction. By doing so, user B is able to not only transmit his/her appear-ance to user A, but also to arrange gestures of the MOBILLI.
